{
  "texts": [
    "He awoke in late June with slightly blurred vision in the LE and was noted to have optic disc edema in the LE at his one-month postoperative visit.",
    "His past medical history included gout, idiopathic cardiomyopathy, congestive heart failure, aortic regurgitation, aortic root dilatation, atrial fibrillation, hyperlipidemia, hypertension, prostate cancer, peripheral vascular disease, and erectile dysfunction.",
    "His medications were allopurinol, alendronate, amiodarone, atorvastatin, doxazosin, fluticasone, furosemide, metoprolol, and rivaroxaban.",
    "He denied symptoms of giant cell arteritis.",
    "He was a former smoker and drank about 1-2 alcoholic beverages several times a week."
  ]
}